{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a274cbbb-d7a5-40c4-9438-517a2176f8b4","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Update your package references** — replace `xunit.runner.visualstudio` with `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Add -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"0.1.2-pre.7\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable — MTP turns your test project into a self-contained app.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Keep `xunit` (2.9.3) and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` as-is.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` works with MTP.\n- Check [xunit docs](https://xunit.net/docs/getting-started/v3/microsoft-testing-platform) for the latest runner package version, as it's still in prerelease.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"784a70c1-0cce-4581-8d5e-7e581a475822","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":397,"requestId":"67CA:2B537A:28DB31B:2D20538:69FD337D"},"id":"3e84f5af-2f26-420f-91de-a2a1797bbe16","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:18.714Z","parentId":"5ea72200-48e9-42ca-9f01-e8628097f4eb"}
